<div class="inner-page">

  <!-- Hero Banner -->
  <div style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1B4332 0%,#2D6A4F 100%);padding:90px 48px;text-align:center;">
    <div style="max-width:700px;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="font-size:11px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.14em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#52B788;margin-bottom:14px;">The Ingredients</div>
      <h1 style="color:#fff;font-size:clamp(34px,5vw,58px);font-weight:900;line-height:1.05;margin:0 0 18px;">Meet the Mushrooms</h1>
      <p style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.8);font-size:17px;line-height:1.65;max-width:560px;margin:0 auto;">Three of nature's most studied functional mushrooms. Dual-extracted for full potency. In every single can.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Mushroom 1: Lion's Mane -->
  <section class="mush-section">
    <div class="mush-inner">
      <div class="mush-badge" style="background:#EEF2FF;color:#3730A3;">FOCUS</div>
      <div class="mush-layout">
        <div class="mush-icon-wrap" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#EEF2FF,#C7D2FE);">
          <div class="mush-emoji">
            <img src="{{ 'lions-mane.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Lion's Mane mushroom" loading="lazy">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mush-content">
          <h2>Lion's Mane</h2>
          <div class="mush-dose">900mg per can · Fruiting body extract</div>
          <p class="mush-desc">Lion's Mane (<em>Hericium erinaceus</em>) is the nootropic mushroom. It's been used in traditional medicine for centuries — now modern research is catching up to why.</p>
          <div class="mush-benefits">
            <div class="mush-benefit">
              <span class="mush-benefit-icon">
                <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#3730A3" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M9 3h6l1 4H8L9 3z"/><path d="M8 7v10a1 1 0 0 0 1 1h6a1 1 0 0 0 1-1V7"/><path d="M12 11v3M11 13h2"/></svg>
              </span>
              <div><strong>Nerve Growth Factor (NGF)</strong><p>Lion's Mane stimulates the production of NGF — a protein critical for the growth, maintenance, and survival of nerve cells. More NGF means better neural connectivity.</p></div>
            </div>
            <div class="mush-benefit">
              <span class="mush-benefit-icon">
                <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#3730A3" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"/><path d="M12 2v3M12 19v3M4.22 4.22l2.12 2.12M17.66 17.66l2.12 2.12M2 12h3M19 12h3M4.22 19.78l2.12-2.12M17.66 6.34l2.12-2.12"/></svg>
              </span>
              <div><strong>Cognitive Clarity</strong><p>Clinical studies show Lion's Mane supplementation improves memory, focus, and mild cognitive function. The effect is subtle but consistent — like sharpening a lens.</p></div>
            </div>
            <div class="mush-benefit">
              <span class="mush-benefit-icon">
                <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#3730A3" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 2L4 6v6c0 5.55 3.84 10.74 8 12 4.16-1.26 8-6.45 8-12V6l-8-4z"/></svg>
              </span>
              <div><strong>Neuroprotection</strong><p>Emerging research shows Lion's Mane may help protect against age-related cognitive decline by supporting myelin sheath integrity.</p></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="mush-fact">
            <strong>Why 900mg?</strong> Most studies showing cognitive benefit used doses of 500–3,000mg daily. At 900mg per can, Happie hits an effective daily dose in a single serving.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="mush-divider"></div>

  <!-- Mushroom 2: Cordyceps -->
  <section class="mush-section" style="background:#FAFAFA;">
    <div class="mush-inner">
      <div class="mush-badge" style="background:#FFF7ED;color:#C2410C;">ENERGY</div>
      <div class="mush-layout">
        <div class="mush-icon-wrap" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#FFF7ED,#FED7AA);">
          <div class="mush-emoji">
            <img src="{{ 'cordyceps.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Cordyceps militaris mushroom" loading="lazy">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mush-content">
          <h2>Cordyceps</h2>
          <div class="mush-dose">700mg per can · Cordyceps militaris · Fruiting body extract</div>
          <p class="mush-desc">Cordyceps (<em>Cordyceps militaris</em>) is the energy mushroom — used by Tibetan herders for altitude endurance and by elite athletes for performance. No caffeine. No adrenal crash.</p>
          <div class="mush-benefits">
            <div class="mush-benefit">
              <span class="mush-benefit-icon">
                <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#C2410C" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 3C8 4 5 8 5 12s3 8 7 9c4-1 7-5 7-9s-3-8-7-9z"/><path d="M12 8v4l2 2"/></svg>
              </span>
              <div><strong>Oxygen Utilization (VO2 Max)</strong><p>Cordyceps increases the body's production of ATP — the molecule that powers cellular energy. Studies show improved VO2 max and oxygen uptake efficiency in athletes.</p></div>
            </div>
            <div class="mush-benefit">
              <span class="mush-benefit-icon">
                <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#C2410C" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M13 2L4.5 13.5H11L10 22l9.5-11.5H13L13 2z"/></svg>
              </span>
              <div><strong>Endurance Without Stimulants</strong><p>Unlike caffeine, Cordyceps doesn't spike cortisol. It works at the mitochondrial level — more efficient energy production means sustained output without the 2pm crash.</p></div>
            </div>
            <div class="mush-benefit">
              <span class="mush-benefit-icon">
                <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#C2410C" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M18 8h1a4 4 0 0 1 0 8h-1"/><path d="M2 8h16v9a4 4 0 0 1-4 4H6a4 4 0 0 1-4-4V8z"/><line x1="6" y1="1" x2="6" y2="4"/><line x1="10" y1="1" x2="10" y2="4"/><line x1="14" y1="1" x2="14" y2="4"/></svg>
              </span>
              <div><strong>Exercise Recovery</strong><p>Cordyceps has been shown to reduce exercise-induced fatigue and support faster recovery by buffering lactic acid buildup in muscle tissue.</p></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="mush-fact">
            <strong>Militaris, not sinensis.</strong> We use <em>Cordyceps militaris</em> — the cultivated species with the highest concentration of Cordycepin, the key active compound. <em>C. sinensis</em> (the parasitic caterpillar fungus) is rare, expensive, and inconsistent.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="mush-divider"></div>

  <!-- Mushroom 3: Reishi -->
  <section class="mush-section">
    <div class="mush-inner">
      <div class="mush-badge" style="background:#F0FDF4;color:#166534;">CALM</div>
      <div class="mush-layout">
        <div class="mush-icon-wrap" style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#F0FDF4,#BBF7D0);">
          <div class="mush-emoji">
            <img src="{{ 'reishi.png' | asset_url }}" alt="Reishi (Ganoderma lucidum) mushroom" loading="lazy">
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mush-content">
          <h2>Reishi</h2>
          <div class="mush-dose">400mg per can · Ganoderma lucidum · Fruiting body extract</div>
          <p class="mush-desc">Reishi (<em>Ganoderma lucidum</em>) is known as the "mushroom of immortality" in traditional Chinese medicine. The adaptogen that brings everything into balance.</p>
          <div class="mush-benefits">
            <div class="mush-benefit">
              <span class="mush-benefit-icon">
                <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#166534" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 22V12"/><path d="M12 12C12 12 7 10 6 6c3 0 6 2 6 6z"/><path d="M12 12c0 0 5-2 6-6-3 0-6 2-6 6z"/></svg>
              </span>
              <div><strong>Stress Adaptation</strong><p>Reishi's triterpenes help modulate the HPA axis — your body's stress response system. Regular use helps your body respond to stress more efficiently rather than overreacting.</p></div>
            </div>
            <div class="mush-benefit">
              <span class="mush-benefit-icon">
                <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#166534" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M21 12.79A9 9 0 1 1 11.21 3 7 7 0 0 0 21 12.79z"/></svg>
              </span>
              <div><strong>Sleep Quality</strong><p>Studies show Reishi can improve sleep latency and total sleep time by supporting GABAergic pathways — the same mechanisms targeted by many sleep medications, but naturally.</p></div>
            </div>
            <div class="mush-benefit">
              <span class="mush-benefit-icon">
                <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#166534" stroke-width="1.75" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 2L4 6v6c0 5.55 3.84 10.74 8 12 4.16-1.26 8-6.45 8-12V6l-8-4z"/><path d="M8.5 12l2.5 2.5 4.5-4.5"/></svg>
              </span>
              <div><strong>Immune Modulation</strong><p>Reishi's beta-glucans are among the most studied immunomodulatory compounds in nature. They don't just boost immunity — they help regulate it for optimal function.</p></div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="mush-fact">
            <strong>The balance mushroom.</strong> While Lion's Mane sharpens and Cordyceps energizes, Reishi keeps you grounded. Together, the three create a stack that's focused and energized — without the edge.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

